1
00:00:13,708 --> 00:00:15,333
(Wooju / Barcode Tinnasit)

2
00:00:18,375 --> 00:00:20,083
(Raon / Jeff Satur)

3
00:00:22,208 --> 00:00:23,833
(Woo-hyuk / DION)

4
00:00:26,042 --> 00:00:27,958
(Q / Q)

5
00:00:30,208 --> 00:00:32,042
(Hachi / Jason) (Air / Alpha)

6
00:00:33,833 --> 00:00:36,893
(Jirong / Kim Namsu, Mr. Kim / Song Wonsu, Chairman Lee /
Choi Sanghak) (Officer Sin / Im Changseop, Mina / Heo Yeseul)

7
00:00:36,917 --> 00:00:41,333
"Wooju Bakery"
(Episode 4)

8
00:00:41,375 --> 00:00:43,583
(Hachi has run away from home)

9
00:00:47,917 --> 00:00:49,500
Is that all?

10
00:00:52,875 --> 00:00:54,542
Hey! Hurry up!

11
00:01:31,542 --> 00:01:32,875
Hurry! Come on!

12
00:01:33,625 --> 00:01:35,025
The quicker you finish
the quicker you get paid.

13
00:01:46,708 --> 00:01:48,625
This feels weird.

14
00:01:49,917 --> 00:01:51,333
What kind of weird?

15
00:01:52,375 --> 00:01:57,125
It feels like when my parents
used to bathe me when I was a kid.

16
00:01:57,625 --> 00:01:59,792
You have memories like that?

17
00:02:01,458 --> 00:02:03,875
No, it's just a feeling.

18
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:06,750
My memories of my
parents are already so blurry.

19
00:02:06,875 --> 00:02:10,917
I can barely recall them.

20
00:02:11,042 --> 00:02:13,333
The doctor said it was
because of that trauma.

21
00:02:13,458 --> 00:02:15,375
A part of my memory is gone.

22
00:02:17,125 --> 00:02:18,667
I see...

23
00:02:19,667 --> 00:02:21,347
I don't have memories of my mother either.

24
00:02:22,042 --> 00:02:22,917
Why?

25
00:02:23,042 --> 00:02:24,458
I hatched from an egg.

26
00:02:24,583 --> 00:02:26,750
So the first thing I saw
when I was born was my dad.

27
00:02:27,167 --> 00:02:30,083
Wow... your amnesia is on another level.

28
00:02:30,208 --> 00:02:31,667
You're not even scrubbing properly.

29
00:02:31,792 --> 00:02:33,125
Turn around.

30
00:02:35,583 --> 00:02:40,667
Seriously, that's not how
we do it on my planet...

31
00:02:40,792 --> 00:02:42,000
Shut up.

32
00:02:54,875 --> 00:02:58,333
This feeling... it's so nice.

33
00:03:25,875 --> 00:03:27,018
That bakery owner right now...

34
00:03:27,042 --> 00:03:28,875
Is he the son of that
guy from 15 years ago?

35
00:03:30,417 --> 00:03:32,792
I don't know, I don't know anything.

36
00:03:32,917 --> 00:03:36,208
You say you don't know.
But you've been living here for 100 years.

37
00:03:36,333 --> 00:03:38,625
There was indeed a
bakery here 15 years ago.

38
00:03:38,750 --> 00:03:41,125
Their bread was really
popular around here back then.

39
00:03:41,250 --> 00:03:44,083
Business was booming before the incident.

40
00:03:44,208 --> 00:03:47,542
I didn't know you were
such a jerk back then.

41
00:03:47,667 --> 00:03:50,375
Hey, you were part of it too, okay?

42
00:03:50,500 --> 00:03:51,833
We built that building together.

43
00:03:51,958 --> 00:03:55,333
I just wanted to go back home.

44
00:03:55,458 --> 00:03:57,625
Yeah, exactly.

45
00:03:57,750 --> 00:03:59,958
You guys go back to your home.

46
00:04:00,083 --> 00:04:03,250
And I'll go make money and become
the richest person in the universe.

47
00:04:03,375 --> 00:04:04,643
That was our deal from the start.

48
00:04:04,667 --> 00:04:08,000
The blueprint you brought
was completely wrong, wasn't it?

49
00:04:08,417 --> 00:04:10,167
That wasn't my fault!

50
00:04:12,292 --> 00:04:15,292
Fine, even if there was
a mistake back then.

51
00:04:15,417 --> 00:04:17,583
Let's just review the
issues from that time.

52
00:04:20,875 --> 00:04:22,958
This is the revised blueprint.

53
00:04:23,875 --> 00:04:26,500
Come on, take another look at this.

54
00:04:26,625 --> 00:04:29,958
You better show me what
you're really capable of this time.

55
00:04:43,125 --> 00:04:45,542
Is my baby hungry?
Do you want something to eat?

56
00:04:52,792 --> 00:04:55,333
You scared me! What are you doing?

57
00:04:55,458 --> 00:04:58,458
That looks delicious, can I have some?

58
00:04:59,250 --> 00:05:01,625
I'm kidding! This is dog food, you know?

59
00:05:14,583 --> 00:05:15,583
(Basic Dog Food)

60
00:05:17,375 --> 00:05:18,667
I like this one!

61
00:05:23,292 --> 00:05:24,692
You look so seductive wearing that.

62
00:05:25,958 --> 00:05:26,667
Where did you buy this?

63
00:05:26,792 --> 00:05:28,851
There's a convenience store
nearby, they sell them there.

64
00:05:28,875 --> 00:05:30,458
Seeing you even wearing dog clothes...

65
00:05:30,583 --> 00:05:32,000
You must really like dogs, right?

66
00:05:32,125 --> 00:05:33,208
Do you have a dog?

67
00:05:40,542 --> 00:05:42,167
- Officer Shin.
- Yes.

68
00:05:43,333 --> 00:05:44,875
That's enough.

69
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:46,458
Let her go.

70
00:05:46,576 --> 00:05:47,785
I wanted to stay here myself.

71
00:05:47,917 --> 00:05:48,958
Please, leave me alone.

72
00:05:49,083 --> 00:05:51,750
Ugh, whatever. Suit yourself.

73
00:05:51,875 --> 00:05:52,875
I'm off the clock.

74
00:05:52,917 --> 00:05:53,917
Okay.

75
00:05:55,542 --> 00:05:57,750
Alright, let's go over this again.

76
00:05:58,125 --> 00:06:00,792
So why did you go to that bakery?

77
00:06:00,917 --> 00:06:03,375
Because I'm an influencer.

78
00:06:03,500 --> 00:06:08,000
I visit every new shop that opens.

79
00:06:08,125 --> 00:06:10,083
It's my responsibility to
inform my subscribers.

80
00:06:10,208 --> 00:06:11,488
So you were there to promote it?

81
00:06:11,542 --> 00:06:13,542
Oh, right... yeah, promotion.

82
00:06:13,667 --> 00:06:15,083
But I didn't expect...

83
00:06:15,208 --> 00:06:17,583
To get bitten by that dog-thing.

84
00:06:17,708 --> 00:06:19,250
That's how I ended up like this.

85
00:06:19,500 --> 00:06:21,500
Are there vicious dogs there?

86
00:06:21,625 --> 00:06:24,708
No, it's not a dog.

87
00:06:24,833 --> 00:06:27,667
It's this... this pervert
wearing a dog mask.

88
00:06:28,958 --> 00:06:31,333
And did he say anything else?

89
00:06:31,458 --> 00:06:34,417
Just stuff like it's a
bakery run by aliens.

90
00:06:34,542 --> 00:06:36,333
I just posted a thumbnail for now.

91
00:06:36,458 --> 00:06:37,792
That's the one.

92
00:06:37,917 --> 00:06:39,226
That perverted jerk in the dog mask.

93
00:06:39,250 --> 00:06:41,000
No, that person...

94
00:06:41,917 --> 00:06:43,417
Must be an alien.

95
00:06:43,667 --> 00:06:44,667
Is... is that so?

96
00:06:44,750 --> 00:06:47,708
But the person who kidnapped
me was someone else.

97
00:06:47,833 --> 00:06:50,417
He bit your finger, that's assault, right?

98
00:06:50,542 --> 00:06:52,250
Let's arrest him and investigate.

99
00:06:52,375 --> 00:06:53,500
When?

100
00:06:53,625 --> 00:06:54,792
Now.

101
00:07:11,792 --> 00:07:12,976
Are we arresting him directly?

102
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:14,000
Of course not.

103
00:07:14,125 --> 00:07:17,500
We wait until he meets with other aliens
and catch him red-handed.

104
00:07:17,625 --> 00:07:18,792
Follow him.

105
00:07:29,458 --> 00:07:30,292
Look over there.

106
00:07:30,417 --> 00:07:32,167
I told you that dog-thing was suspicious.

107
00:07:35,833 --> 00:07:37,875
Hi, little doggy!

108
00:07:38,833 --> 00:07:42,458
Are you doing fine here? I'll see you... later...

109
00:07:46,083 --> 00:07:47,167
Customer.

110
00:07:47,292 --> 00:07:49,125
Is there something you're looking for?

111
00:07:49,243 --> 00:07:50,719
This one! I'm looking for this one!

112
00:07:50,750 --> 00:07:51,790
Oh, so you're a foreigner.

113
00:07:51,875 --> 00:07:53,667
You need to pay first.

114
00:07:53,792 --> 00:07:55,250
Here, take it!

115
00:07:57,875 --> 00:07:59,417
Boss, that's dog food!

116
00:07:59,542 --> 00:08:01,250
You'll get sick if you eat that.

117
00:08:01,375 --> 00:08:02,750
I told you, you can't eat that!

118
00:08:02,875 --> 00:08:03,917
You can't eat this!

119
00:08:04,042 --> 00:08:05,292
You'll really get into trouble.

120
00:08:08,208 --> 00:08:09,667
Gotcha!

121
00:08:11,542 --> 00:08:13,042
What are you guys doing?

122
00:08:16,542 --> 00:08:17,958
Got this one too!

123
00:08:18,417 --> 00:08:20,583
Oh yeah, jackpot!

124
00:08:20,708 --> 00:08:22,250
What is this!?

125
00:08:22,833 --> 00:08:24,375
(Wooju Bakery)

126
00:08:45,042 --> 00:08:46,208
Um...

127
00:08:46,958 --> 00:08:50,000
Raon, are you asleep?

128
00:08:50,583 --> 00:08:53,458
No, I'm not.

129
00:08:53,833 --> 00:08:55,708
There's something I want to ask you...

130
00:08:56,625 --> 00:08:57,625
Yeah, go ahead.

131
00:08:57,708 --> 00:09:03,375
Woo-hyuk and... that princess... uh...

132
00:09:03,500 --> 00:09:04,833
Do they really get along?

133
00:09:08,667 --> 00:09:10,625
We get along pretty well too, don't we?

134
00:09:12,500 --> 00:09:14,083
I'm such a fool for asking you!

135
00:09:20,875 --> 00:09:22,333
Boss, come in quickly!

136
00:09:23,583 --> 00:09:24,875
What?

137
00:09:27,250 --> 00:09:28,500
Hachi has dissapeared.

138
00:09:28,625 --> 00:09:30,292
Hachi really dissapeared!

139
00:09:30,417 --> 00:09:31,542
For real?

140
00:09:31,667 --> 00:09:32,667
Hachi is really missing?

141
00:09:32,750 --> 00:09:33,583
Yeah.

142
00:09:33,708 --> 00:09:36,917
Answer me, what is your relationship?

143
00:09:37,042 --> 00:09:40,292
How many times do I have to say it?
We met for the first time today.

144
00:09:40,417 --> 00:09:43,292
He's just a customer who came to
our convenience store to buy something.

145
00:09:43,875 --> 00:09:45,500
You bit this person, didn't you?

146
00:09:45,625 --> 00:09:47,500
That constitutes assault.

147
00:09:49,208 --> 00:09:52,917
You dare look at me? You bit
my finger and made it look like this!

148
00:09:53,042 --> 00:09:55,083
Looks like we'll be
investigating all night.

149
00:09:55,208 --> 00:09:58,542
Can a police officer just drag innocent
people in for questioning like this?

150
00:09:58,667 --> 00:10:02,417
Aliens must follow Earth's
laws when they come here.

151
00:10:02,542 --> 00:10:04,667
Stop talking so much.

152
00:10:04,792 --> 00:10:07,417
W-what, aliens?

153
00:10:07,542 --> 00:10:10,833
Officer, what are you doing?
Let me go!

154
00:10:10,958 --> 00:10:12,976
We don't even have a part-timer now,
the store is a mess.

155
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:16,750
Wait a second. We're going
to do an alien identification test.

156
00:10:17,292 --> 00:10:21,792
Aliens who have been on Earth for a long
time are hard to distinguish from humans.

157
00:10:21,917 --> 00:10:25,792
The easiest way is a blood test.

158
00:10:25,917 --> 00:10:27,292
Let's start with a blood test.

159
00:10:27,417 --> 00:10:30,333
Right, let's check your
body temperature first.

160
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:32,792
Are you really a police officer?

161
00:10:32,917 --> 00:10:35,167
Are you going to draw blood
from innocent people now?

162
00:10:36,292 --> 00:10:37,292
Hachi!

163
00:10:37,375 --> 00:10:38,708
Come out!

164
00:10:39,333 --> 00:10:40,500
Hachi!

165
00:10:40,625 --> 00:10:42,042
Come here.

166
00:10:42,917 --> 00:10:44,167
Hachi!

167
00:10:49,375 --> 00:10:51,000
Hachi!

168
00:10:51,125 --> 00:10:52,125
Come out!

169
00:10:53,917 --> 00:10:55,042
Hachi!

170
00:10:55,167 --> 00:10:56,375
Come out.

171
00:11:17,500 --> 00:11:18,934
Please, no blood please.

172
00:11:18,959 --> 00:11:20,876
I'm scared of blood please, no blood...

173
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:22,559
There should be a thermometer
in the warehouse over there.

174
00:11:22,583 --> 00:11:24,423
There should be a
breathalyzer or thermometer.

175
00:11:24,500 --> 00:11:27,042
Wait, this person looks like a foreigner.
Is this really okay?

176
00:11:27,167 --> 00:11:29,083
Which country are you from?

177
00:11:29,108 --> 00:11:30,850
I came from a country far away from here.

178
00:11:30,875 --> 00:11:32,250
See, see!

179
00:11:32,375 --> 00:11:34,458
He said he's from very far away.

180
00:11:34,583 --> 00:11:36,768
No way, the South Korean police
are treating a foreign tourist like this?

181
00:11:36,792 --> 00:11:38,292
Isn't this illegal?

182
00:11:38,417 --> 00:11:39,917
Watch them for me for a second.

183
00:11:40,042 --> 00:11:40,917
I'm going to get the thermometer.

184
00:11:41,042 --> 00:11:42,208
Okay.

185
00:11:44,708 --> 00:11:46,788
Do you think the handcuffs
will just open like that?

186
00:11:46,833 --> 00:11:49,375
You bit my finger, so
you have to pay the price.

187
00:11:49,500 --> 00:11:51,042
What on earth are you doing?

188
00:11:58,500 --> 00:12:00,625
So you're a magician.

189
00:12:00,750 --> 00:12:03,625
Wait... Officer! This guy is getting away!

190
00:12:03,750 --> 00:12:05,458
Hey! How are we supposed to find him?

191
00:12:08,042 --> 00:12:09,542
Officer! Hey!

192
00:12:11,535 --> 00:12:13,785
Catch him! Hurry up and catch him!

193
00:12:13,917 --> 00:12:15,958
Catch him!

194
00:12:27,625 --> 00:12:30,000
It's so late, where could
that dog have gone?

195
00:12:30,542 --> 00:12:32,167
This has never happened before...

196
00:12:33,042 --> 00:12:36,333
Hey, when was the last time you saw Hachi?

197
00:12:37,292 --> 00:12:41,333
I don't know, he was just DJing all night.

198
00:12:45,875 --> 00:12:47,795
Searching aimlessly
like this is so inefficient.

199
00:12:50,417 --> 00:12:52,458
Think about what that dog might like.

200
00:12:52,576 --> 00:12:54,535
Not a dog, it's Hachi!

201
00:12:54,667 --> 00:12:56,125
He's not a dog.

202
00:12:56,500 --> 00:12:57,958
But...

203
00:12:59,375 --> 00:13:03,083
He seems to like what dogs like.

204
00:13:06,792 --> 00:13:08,192
Should we split up to look for him?

205
00:13:08,292 --> 00:13:12,250
What? You aren't thinking of...

206
00:13:16,125 --> 00:13:20,375
Colluding with that dog to
make a run for it, are you?

207
00:13:20,500 --> 00:13:22,125
Absolutely not!

208
00:13:22,250 --> 00:13:24,000
You stay right by my side, got it?

209
00:13:24,125 --> 00:13:26,167
I mean what I say.

210
00:13:26,292 --> 00:13:27,833
A prince should follow the rules.

211
00:13:28,333 --> 00:13:30,250
A prince? Stop talking nonsense.

212
00:13:31,708 --> 00:13:33,208
Don't you dare leave my side!

213
00:13:33,326 --> 00:13:34,386
OK OK.

214
00:13:34,417 --> 00:13:39,500
I'm going this way, you
guys go that way. OK?

215
00:13:41,250 --> 00:13:42,750
I am a noble prince, after all.

216
00:13:42,875 --> 00:13:44,625
I won't run away until I find Hachi.

217
00:13:45,458 --> 00:13:46,750
Let's go together!

218
00:13:47,542 --> 00:13:49,083
Officer Shin.

219
00:13:49,208 --> 00:13:50,542
What about the suspect?

220
00:13:51,458 --> 00:13:53,542
I'm heading back to
the station, wait for me.

221
00:13:53,667 --> 00:13:54,792
Got it.

222
00:13:56,625 --> 00:13:57,750
What kind of suspect is it?

223
00:13:57,875 --> 00:14:00,125
The guy in the dog suit.
The one from Wooju Bakery.

224
00:14:00,250 --> 00:14:03,125
I've got the other one tied up
tight, he's not going anywhere.

225
00:14:03,250 --> 00:14:04,583
Understood.

226
00:14:08,750 --> 00:14:10,583
Sorry, let me untie you right away.

227
00:14:13,125 --> 00:14:16,565
You catch them and then just let them go?
One escaped, and you let the other one loose.

228
00:14:17,583 --> 00:14:20,167
The South Korean police
are truly something else.

229
00:14:20,833 --> 00:14:22,625
What were the blood test results?

230
00:14:23,208 --> 00:14:26,083
It's B positive.

231
00:14:26,708 --> 00:14:28,375
So, is he an alien?

232
00:14:29,458 --> 00:14:30,208
No.

233
00:14:30,333 --> 00:14:33,333
If you dare mention the word
'alien' in front of me again...

234
00:14:33,458 --> 00:14:34,458
But, senior, however...

235
00:14:34,583 --> 00:14:36,167
You're still...!

236
00:14:36,292 --> 00:14:41,292
They didn't just handcuff
me, they taped my mouth shut!

237
00:14:41,458 --> 00:14:45,458
Isn't that a human rights
violation and torture?

238
00:14:45,750 --> 00:14:48,583
Sir, we are truly sorry. We
don't even know what to say.

239
00:14:48,708 --> 00:14:52,000
Enough! I'm going to report everything
you've done to the news stations.

240
00:14:52,125 --> 00:14:54,245
Do the South Korean police
have nothing better to do?

241
00:14:54,333 --> 00:14:55,667
Playing some kind of alien game?

242
00:14:55,792 --> 00:14:58,000
It was truly our mistake,
we are very sorry.

243
00:14:58,125 --> 00:15:02,208
But sir, that companion
who came with you...

244
00:15:02,333 --> 00:15:03,333
Do you know him?

245
00:15:03,417 --> 00:15:07,583
No. He was just a foreign customer who came
to our convenience store to buy something.

246
00:15:07,708 --> 00:15:09,958
But he did look a bit like a magician.

247
00:15:12,167 --> 00:15:15,792
That guy isn't a magician, he's indeed an alien.

248
00:15:16,500 --> 00:15:19,542
An alien from a planet far, far away.

249
00:15:19,667 --> 00:15:20,875
An alien?

250
00:15:29,667 --> 00:15:32,250
Alright, everyone go home.

251
00:15:32,375 --> 00:15:35,792
Just pretend today never happened.

252
00:15:35,917 --> 00:15:37,208
Bye.

253
00:15:39,958 --> 00:15:41,083
Wait...

254
00:15:45,125 --> 00:15:47,375
No, seriously, what exactly is that gun?

255
00:15:47,500 --> 00:15:48,708
This?

256
00:15:49,625 --> 00:15:52,708
It's probably hard to understand
using Earth's scientific knowledge.

257
00:15:52,833 --> 00:15:54,750
Earth's scientific knowledge?

258
00:15:56,708 --> 00:15:58,125
Don't worry.

259
00:15:59,708 --> 00:16:01,375
I won't shoot you.

260
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:08,167
Is he still at the police station?

261
00:16:08,292 --> 00:16:10,417
He was there a moment ago, but he escaped.

262
00:16:10,542 --> 00:16:12,208
We're looking for him now, too.

263
00:16:12,333 --> 00:16:13,667
No.

264
00:16:13,792 --> 00:16:15,000
We have to find him quickly.

265
00:16:15,125 --> 00:16:17,792
Because... he's a foreigner.

266
00:16:17,917 --> 00:16:19,101
He doesn't speak the language well.

267
00:16:19,125 --> 00:16:20,375
Don't worry too much.

268
00:16:20,500 --> 00:16:21,833
We'll find him soon.

269
00:16:21,958 --> 00:16:23,833
I'll help look for him too.

270
00:16:23,958 --> 00:16:26,042
Oh, okay...

271
00:16:26,958 --> 00:16:28,083
Thanksz.

272
00:16:30,542 --> 00:16:32,042
We have to find him first.

273
00:16:32,167 --> 00:16:34,917
Otherwise, if he gets caught
again, they'll dissect him.

274
00:16:35,042 --> 00:16:38,250
Hey, why would the police dissect you?

275
00:16:38,708 --> 00:16:39,500
You're not frogs.

276
00:16:39,625 --> 00:16:46,167
That's been a rumor where
we're from for a long time.

277
00:16:47,833 --> 00:16:49,333
You're actually buying into that?

278
00:16:49,917 --> 00:16:51,708
Were you raised in a bamboo forest?

279
00:16:53,167 --> 00:16:56,042
No wonder you believe such nonsense!

280
00:16:58,167 --> 00:16:59,792
A bamboo forest? What's that...

281
00:17:02,125 --> 00:17:03,500
Let's go!

282
00:17:11,917 --> 00:17:12,750
What is that?

283
00:17:12,875 --> 00:17:14,083
What?

284
00:17:17,792 --> 00:17:18,917
That's a playground, right?

285
00:17:19,542 --> 00:17:22,792
A playground? What's that for?

286
00:17:22,917 --> 00:17:25,917
It's a place for kids to play.

287
00:17:26,208 --> 00:17:30,000
What? What backwater place were you raised in
that you don't even know what a playground is?

288
00:17:30,458 --> 00:17:32,375
Want to play here for a bit before we go?

289
00:17:35,083 --> 00:17:40,042
This is my first time seeing a playground.

290
00:17:40,167 --> 00:17:41,500
When I was little,

291
00:17:43,833 --> 00:17:45,313
I always wanted to play with friends.

292
00:17:45,375 --> 00:17:47,042
That was my wish.

293
00:17:52,792 --> 00:17:54,125
I'm sorry.

294
00:17:56,375 --> 00:17:59,958
But, you and I aren't friends, are we?

295
00:18:00,083 --> 00:18:02,625
Do you want to play with me?

296
00:18:02,750 --> 00:18:05,458
I'm your employer, your boss!

297
00:18:07,500 --> 00:18:08,500
I know, I know.

298
00:18:09,333 --> 00:18:10,958
Can't a boss be friends with me?

299
00:18:14,292 --> 00:18:19,917
Your eyes... they look like
the Earth I saw from space.

300
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:25,250
W-what?

301
00:18:25,375 --> 00:18:26,750
They're beautiful.

302
00:18:28,833 --> 00:18:30,250
Stop that!

303
00:18:34,875 --> 00:18:36,500
You're a weirdo.

304
00:18:36,625 --> 00:18:40,542
Fine, I'll play with you for a bit.

305
00:18:40,667 --> 00:18:42,387
Since it's your first time at a playground,

306
00:18:43,208 --> 00:18:45,833
and you don't have any friends,
I'll keep you company, okay?

307
00:18:45,958 --> 00:18:47,375
Have you ever been on a slide?

308
00:19:18,542 --> 00:19:20,417
Wait for me!

309
00:19:36,833 --> 00:19:38,917
You really can't read the room, can you?

310
00:19:39,042 --> 00:19:41,500
The mood is perfect,
why go and interrupt them?

311
00:19:44,083 --> 00:19:45,833
We still have to tell him.

312
00:19:47,833 --> 00:19:49,667
He looks like he's having a great time.

313
00:19:49,792 --> 00:19:51,042
Our Wooju,

314
00:19:51,167 --> 00:19:53,625
he's actually really worried, isn't he?

315
00:19:55,042 --> 00:19:57,208
Does that look like he's worried?

316
00:19:57,917 --> 00:20:01,083
He looks like he's having a blast to me.

317
00:20:01,208 --> 00:20:03,292
How long are you going to
keep worrying about him?

318
00:20:18,958 --> 00:20:20,542
Woo-hoo!

319
00:20:23,292 --> 00:20:26,292
Oh, merciful and great gods,

320
00:20:26,417 --> 00:20:28,833
I am your loyal follower.

321
00:20:28,958 --> 00:20:32,917
Oh, for heaven's sake...

322
00:20:33,042 --> 00:20:34,625
Vice President Oh!

323
00:20:35,542 --> 00:20:36,917
God bless us.

324
00:20:37,333 --> 00:20:41,167
Are you praying for us?

325
00:20:42,583 --> 00:20:45,625
It seems the gods of
Earth are truly powerful.

326
00:20:45,750 --> 00:20:47,958
Look, they both got released, didn't they?

327
00:20:48,083 --> 00:20:50,000
That was Chairman Lee who let them go.

328
00:20:50,125 --> 00:20:52,125
Chairman Lee isn't a god.

329
00:20:52,250 --> 00:20:54,000
Alright, enough of that.

330
00:20:55,542 --> 00:21:00,333
But do we really have to
do what Chairman Lee said?

331
00:21:00,458 --> 00:21:02,875
We'll be punished by the gods
of Earth if we do bad things.

332
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:03,833
Vice President Oh,

333
00:21:03,958 --> 00:21:07,083
this is the only way we can get back home.

334
00:21:07,208 --> 00:21:08,500
You're right.

335
00:21:10,458 --> 00:21:11,000
These two...

336
00:21:11,125 --> 00:21:12,184
they don't understand anything.

337
00:21:12,208 --> 00:21:14,292
It's not like there's no other way.
